$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Soohyeon, are you okay?
Soohyeon: I... I'm fine. Thankfully, I ran into you...
Soohyeon: Thank you for your help.
Juan Yun: Why did you run here all alone? Did the dances end? Where is Yonghyeon?
Soohyeon: I... I was looking for something... Yonghyeon was here, but we were separated. Anyway, I should keep looking!
Juan Yun: No! It's too dangerous out there! What's so important?
Soohyeon: My talisman...
Juan Yun: Talisman? The one you're always carrying?
Soohyeon: Yes. I looked all through the crowd but still couldn't find it. What am I supposed to do? If I lose it...
Juan Yun: Don't cry, don't cry... There's no need to get worked up. How about I look for it with you?
Tindoiimu: Not a good idea... Those people who just attacked us were bewitched. There must be a bewitcher around, and if we run into them...
Soohyeon: Tindoiimu, Juan Yun, please let me go!
Soohyeon: That... that talisman is very, very important to me. I can't lose it...
Tindoiimu: I'm not trying to stop you, I'm just saying wait a—
???: What are you doing to Kong Soohyeon!?
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon! It's not what you think, they've done nothing!
Yonghyeon: Who are you trying to fool!? Look at you! You're crying, you're face is a mess, and you say they've done nothing!?
Soohyeon: My face is a mess...?
Soohyeon: Really, it's a misunderstanding! Tindoiimu and Juan Yun just saved me...
Yonghyeon: Lord Juan Yun?
Juan Yun: Hello, Yonghyeon. Yes, I've been here this whole time~
Yonghyeon: It really is the lord. I was so panicked I didn't even realize it was you...
Soohyeon: See now? They're helping me.
Soohyeon: I was nervous, about to go look for my talisman again... But they said it was too dangerous. They stopped me.
Yonghyeon: Oh, right—your talisman.
Yonghyeon: I've got it right here.
Soohyeon: You found it!? Thank you so much!
Yonghyeon: I finally found it in the crowd—took me ages. Keep it somewhere safe, will ya!?
Juan Yun: Well then, Soohyeon can be at ease now~
Soohyeon: Yes! Thank you again for your help!
Yonghyeon: Wait a second! Soohyeon, you've gotta be more careful!
Yonghyeon: I'll say it right up front—I'm not as naive as Soohyeon. You may have saved her, but that doesn't mean you're innocent!
Tindoiimu: ...Innocent?
Jihasaha: Show some respect, punk!
Juan Yun: Let's all remain calm. Yonghyeon, did you say "innocent"? Did something happen?
Yonghyeon: ...You still don't know?
Yonghyeon: General Yu of the Tiger Tribe was assassinated at the Peace Ceremony.
Juan Yun: What!?
Yonghyeon: And the killer's still out there. Everyone's afraid there's an insect assassin—that's why they're all running for their lives!
Jihasaha: Hold on, if you haven't caught the assassin, then why assume it's someone from the Insect Tribe!?
Yonghyeon: Because! General Yu was the great hero who finally managed to suppress those rotten bugs!
Yonghyeon: And he patrolled the insect borders without mercy, punishing all who stood in his way—who else could it be but one of those maggots!?
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon, you can't just falsely accuse others...
Yonghyeon: Why are you defending them? Aren't you afraid of the Insect Tribe?
Soohyeon: I am afraid of them... but, Princess Tindoiimu isn't the one who attacked mom all those years ago...
Juan Yun: Soonyeoh is right, Yonghyeon. You have no proof. It's not right to wildly accuse others.
Yonghyeon: No proof!? Soohyeon, didn't you see the assassin!?
Soohyeon: ...I didn't see them clearly. There were too many people...
Yonghyeon: Dammit... if I had chased 'em then they wouldn't have gotten away! It's all your fault for making me look for your stupid talisman!
Soohyeon: I-I'm sorry. I was so scared...
Yonghyeon: Then you freak out and run all over the place—How was I supposed to find you!?
Yonghyeon: What if I ran into those bewitchers!? How would you feel then, huh!?
Soohyeon: ...*sob*...
Juan Yun: Yonghyeon, you can't lose your temper on a woman...
Soohyeon: I admit I made a mistake... but I didn't force you to help me. Yonghyeon, why are you always so mean to me?
Yonghyeon: I... ugh, talking to you is impossible!
Yonghyeon: Point is, I'm bringing the bug princess in for questioning!
Tingko: Absolutely not!
Jihasaha: You want the princess? Then you have to get through me first!
Jiyanama: Where are you taking me!?
???: Shut up! Who said you could ask questions!?
Tindoiimu: (That voice... is that Jiyanama?)
Jiyanama: B-But you can't just snatch up people as you like. You need a reason!
Elite Tiger Soldier: I told you to shut up, lady! You deaf!?
Tindoiimu: Stop it!
Tingko: Jiyanama, wake up!
Tindoiimu: What makes you monsters think you can just—
Juan Yun: Lord of the Qilin Tribe, Juan Yun, at your service. How are you fine fellows doing?
Juan Yun: By the look of those outfits, you're Tiger Tribe Special Forces. The elite of the elite.
Elite Tiger Soldier: ...The mythical Qilin Tribe? What business does the qilin lord have with us?
Juan Yun: It's like this. This woman is the Insect Tribe princess' nanny. They are under the supervision of my tribe. They can't leave qilin territory.
Juan Yun: So, I must ask. Where are you two taking her? And whose commands are you following?
Elite Tiger Soldier: ...Recently, when our troops were out capturing members of the Insect Tribe's resistance movement,

Elite Tiger Soldier: there were several times when they knew of our actions beforehand. 

The brilliant General Yu suspected that someone was leaking military information to the enemy.
Juan Yun: Could it be...

Elite Tiger Soldier: The general has been out on war expeditions for many years. 

That he returned to attend the ceremony is just an excuse. He actually returned to catch the mole.
Elite Tiger Soldier: And this insect is one of those spies!
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama is... a spy!?
Tindoiimu: ...No, that's impossible! That would endanger every member of our tribe...
Juan Yun: Gentlemen, there must be some mistake...
Elite Tiger Soldier: That will all be determined after we bring her to General Yu for questioning!
Yonghyeon: You two were just in qilin territory, and you still haven't heard?
Elite Tiger Soldier: Huh? You got something to say then say it!
Yonghyeon: General Yu has been assassinated.
Elite Tiger Soldier: What the...!? Say that again!?
